        <h2>About</h2>
        <p lang="eng">Canada began as 4 provinces hugging the St. Lawrence but grew to become 10 provinces and 3 territories. Each time Canada changed, its leaders debated the purposes, benefits, and drawbacks of Confederation. With the assistance of Canadians from across the country and the globe, <em>The Confederation
Debates</em> digitized and preserved all of these records for Canada 150.</p>
        <p lang="fr">c'est une test</p>

        <p lang="eng"></p>

    </div>

